\title{Separable field extension}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-22}
\taxon{definition}

\p{A field extension #{\kk / \FF} is called \define{Separable} if the minimal polynomial #{m_{\alpha}(x)} is [separable](nt-0025) for all #{\alpha\in\kk}.}

\p{\textbf{Exercise:} Prove or find a counter example: a field #{\FF} of characteristic zero have every finite extension #{\kk / \FF} be separable.}